1
00:00:00,709 --> 00:00:02,544
What I want...

2
00:00:03,503 --> 00:00:05,463
What's most important to me

3
00:00:08,341 --> 00:00:12,429
is that I have a guarantee.
No more attempts on my father's life.

4
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:16,808
What guarantees can I give you?
I'm the hunted onel

5
00:00:17,016 --> 00:00:20,478
I missed my chance.
You think too much of me, kid.

6
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:22,897
I'm not that clever.

7
00:00:24,441 --> 00:00:26,609
All I want is a truce.

8
00:00:33,116 --> 00:00:36,911
I have to go to the bathroom.
Is it all right?

9
00:00:38,538 --> 00:00:41,124
When you got to go, you got to go.

10
00:00:46,337 --> 00:00:47,922
He's clean.

11
00:00:48,548 --> 00:00:50,425
Don't take too long.

12
00:00:53,553 --> 00:00:55,513
I've frisked a thousand punks.

13
00:03:11,107 --> 00:03:17,196
This isn't like the army! You have to get
close and get their brains on your suit.

14
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:20,408
You're taking this very personal.

15
00:03:20,491 --> 00:03:23,995
Tom, this is business
and he's taking it personal.

16
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:27,665
- Where does it say you can't kill a cop?
- Mikey...

17
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:33,921
I'm talking about a cop who's mixed up
in drugs, a dishonest cop.

18
00:03:34,797 --> 00:03:38,634
A cop who got mixed up in the rackets
and got what was coming.

19
00:03:39,177 --> 00:03:43,556
That's a terrific story. We have
newspaper people on the payroll, right?

20
00:03:45,224 --> 00:03:49,020
- They might like a story like that.
- They might.

21
00:03:52,690 --> 00:03:56,194
It's not personal, Sonny.
It's strictly business.

22
00:03:59,322 --> 00:04:01,032
It's as cold as they come.

23
00:04:01,115 --> 00:04:04,535
Impossible to trace,
SO you don't worry about prints.

24
00:04:04,660 --> 00:04:08,706
I put a special tape on the trigger
and the butt. Try it.

25
00:04:21,093 --> 00:04:23,179
Is the trigger too tight?

26
00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:27,642
My ears!

27
00:04:27,725 --> 00:04:32,313
I left it noisy, so it scares away any
pain-in-the-ass innocent bystanders.

28
00:04:33,523 --> 00:04:36,359
You've shot them both.
Now what do you do?

29
00:04:38,861 --> 00:04:42,490
- Sit down, finish my dinner.
- Don't fool around.

30
00:04:42,573 --> 00:04:46,202
Let your hand drop to your side
and let the gun slip out.

31
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:50,581
Everybody will still think you've got it.
They'll stare at your face,

32
00:04:50,706 --> 00:04:53,543
so walk out fast, but don't run.

33
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:57,004
Don't look anybody in the eye,
but don't look away either.

34
00:04:57,088 --> 00:05:00,466
They'll be scared stiff,
so don't worry about nothing.

35
00:05:02,718 --> 00:05:07,098
You'll be all right. You'll take
a vacation, nobody knows where,

36
00:05:07,181 --> 00:05:09,225
and we'll catch the hell.

37
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:13,562
- How bad do you think it will be?
- Pretty goddamn bad.

38
00:05:13,688 --> 00:05:16,774
All the other families will probably
line up against us.

39
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:22,363
These things have to happen every five,
10 years. Gets rid of the bad blood.

40
00:05:22,488 --> 00:05:27,034
Been 10 years since the last one.
You have to stop them at the beginning.

41
00:05:27,159 --> 00:05:32,665
Like they should have stopped Hitler in
Munich, not letting him get away with it.

42
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:38,754
You know, Mike, we were all proud
of you. Being a hero and all.

43
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:40,423
Your father too.

44
00:05:51,183 --> 00:05:55,938
Michael, you lousy bastard!
You killed my husband.

45
00:05:56,022 --> 00:06:00,151
You waited until Papa died,
SO nobody could stop you.

46
00:06:00,234 --> 00:06:03,279
You blamed him for Sonny.
Everybody did.

47
00:06:03,404 --> 00:06:09,160
But you never thought about mel
Now what are we going to do?

48
00:06:09,243 --> 00:06:10,786
Connie.

49
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:15,750
Why do you think
he kept Carlo at the Mall?

50
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:18,669
He knew he was going to kill him.

51
00:06:18,794 --> 00:06:24,175
And you stood godfather to our baby.
You lousy cold-hearted bastard!

52
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:28,387
Want to know how many men he had
Killed with Carlo? Read the papers!

53
00:06:28,471 --> 00:06:31,223
That's your husband,
that's your husband!

54
00:06:40,816 --> 00:06:45,029
No! No, no...

55
00:06:45,112 --> 00:06:48,616
Take her upstairs. Get her a doctor.

56
00:07:09,637 --> 00:07:11,347
She's hysterical.

57
00:07:15,893 --> 00:07:17,770
Hysterical.

58
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,898
Michael, is it true?

59
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:26,987
- Don't ask me about my business, Kay.
- Is it true?

60
00:07:27,112 --> 00:07:29,782
Don't ask me about my business.
Enough!

61
00:07:49,927 --> 00:07:51,554
All right.

62
00:07:54,306 --> 00:07:55,975
This one time.

63
00:07:59,895 --> 00:08:02,690
This one time
I'll let you ask me about my affairs.

64
00:08:09,321 --> 00:08:10,656
Is it true?

65
00:08:14,827 --> 00:08:16,495
Is it?

66
00:08:18,205 --> 00:08:19,665
No.

67
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:36,473
I guess we both need a drink. Come on.

68
00:09:07,838 --> 00:09:09,465
Don Corleone.

